  "description": "<a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p620926/\"><img src=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/2009/images/rss_shuangyu.gif\" style=\"border: 0;\" /></a><br /><p>\n\t<span style=\"color: rgb(128,0,128); line-height: 1.8em;\"><img alt=\"Just like old times &lt;i&gt;(Image: Reuters/Reinhard Krause)&lt;/i&gt;\" src=\"http://www.newscientist.com/data/images/ns/cms/mg22229632.600/mg22229632.600-1_300.jpg\" title=\"Just like old times &lt;i&gt;(Image: Reuters/Reinhard Krause)&lt;/i&gt;\" /></span></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"color: rgb(128,0,128); line-height: 1.8em;\"><strong><a href=\"http://bulo.hujiang.com/menu/15399/\" target=\"_blank\">《英闻天天译》</a></strong></span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">是一档沪江部落的原创翻译互动节目（</span><span style=\"color: rgb(128,0,128); line-height: 1.8em;\"><a href=\"http://bulo.hujiang.com/menu/15399/item/898673/\"><strong>戳去参与节目&gt;&gt;&gt;</strong></a></span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">），主持人提供翻译参考文本，对大家递交的翻译作品进行点评，和大家共同进步！本期节目选取的是关于</span>经济影响文学<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">的</span><span style=\"font-family: verdana, helvetica; color: rgb(51,51,51); line-height: 28px;\">一则英文报道，让我们一起在翻译中关注</span><font color=\"#333333\" style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">。</font></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"color: #000;\"><b style=\"font-family: verdana, helvetica; color: rgb(0,0,0); line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"border-top: 0px;\"><span style=\"border-top: 0px; font-family: verdana, helvetica; border-right: 0px; border-bottom: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-left: 0px; margin: 0px; border-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px;\">SUMMARY：</span></span></b></span></p>\n<div id=\"cke_pastebin\">\n\t<span>在工业革命之前中国就开始使用煤炭</span></div>\n<div>\n\t&nbsp;</div>\n<div>\n\t<strong style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">CONTENT：</strong></div>\n<div id=\"cke_pastebin\">\n\t<div id=\"cke_pastebin\">\n\t\t<div id=\"cke_pastebin\">\n\t\t\t<div id=\"cke_pastebin\">\n\t\t\t\t<div id=\"cke_pastebin\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"cke_pastebin\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"cke_pastebin\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"cke_pastebin\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"cke_pastebin\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"cke_pastebin\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"cke_pastebin\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tCHINA now consumes nearly as much coal as the rest of the world combined. And perhaps it always did: it seems coal was routinely burned 3500 years ago in what is now China &ndash; the earliest evidence we have for the practice.<br />\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tJohn Dodson at the Australian Nuclear Science and Technology Organisation in Sydney, and his colleagues in China, were examining early evidence of bronze <a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"http://dict.hjenglish.com/w/cast\" target=\"_blank\">cast</a>ing in northern China when they found <a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"http://dict.hjenglish.com/w/chunk\" target=\"_blank\">chunk</a>s of burned coal in the ancient <a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"http://dict.hjenglish.com/w/slag\" target=\"_blank\">slag</a> piles instead of the <a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"http://dict.hjenglish.com/w/charcoal\" target=\"_blank\">charcoal</a> they expected. &quot;We got one of the guys to take samples and he <a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"http://dict.hjenglish.com/w/sieve\" target=\"_blank\">sieve</a>d out some seeds, which we <a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"http://dict.hjenglish.com/w/radiocarbon\" target=\"_blank\">radiocarbon</a> dated in Sydney,&quot; says Dodson. The seeds were chosen because they formed at the time the coal was burned, whereas the coal formed millions of years earlier. &quot;You can't just radiocarbon date the coal because it is already ancient carbon,&quot; he says.</div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t&nbsp;</div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n</div>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"color: rgb(0,100,0);\"><strong>【沪江英语小编】</strong></span>大家在查看主持人提供的翻译版本前，可以先自己进行尝试翻译练习，只有在不断的翻译中翻译能力才能有所提升哦！<br />\n\t轻松注册沪江，马上参与<a href=\"http://bulo.hujiang.com/menu/15399/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>【英闻天天译】</strong></a>节目练翻译&rarr;<a href=\"http://pass.hujiang.com/signup/?source=en_sqyd&amp;url=http://bulo.hujiang.com/menu/15399/\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://i2.w.yun.hjfile.cn/doc/201304/810ca373cf4442a188b39dd8ff64425f.jpg\" /></a></p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>本期节目参考译文：</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(128,128,128);\">（参考译文由该节目主持人提供，仅供参考，欢迎大家讨论）</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"color: #000;\"><strong>参考译文1：</strong></span></p>\n<div class=\"replyview red\">\n\t<div id=\"cke_pastebin\">\n\t\t<div id=\"cke_pastebin\">\n\t\t\t<div id=\"cke_pastebin\">\n\t\t\t\t<div id=\"cke_pastebin\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"cke_pastebin\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"cke_pastebin\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"cke_pastebin\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"cke_pastebin\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"cke_pastebin\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"cke_pastebin\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span style=\"color: #000;\">中国现在消费煤的数量几乎和世界上其他地区的综合一样多。也许一直以来便是如此。中国早在3500年前就有燃烧煤炭的习惯，这个习惯也一直保留至今，我们已经找到了最早的证据。<br />\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t悉尼的澳大利亚核科学和技术组织的约翰&middot;多得森和他的同事在中国北方寻找最早的青铜铸件证据时他们在古老的碳渣堆发现燃烧过的煤块，而不是他们期望的木炭。多得森说&ldquo;我们其中的一位进行采样，他筛选出了一些种子，我们回悉尼对其进行放射性碳元素检测追溯日期。&rdquo;之所以选取这些种子是因为它们是在碳燃烧的时候形成的，虽然媒体的形成早在数百万年前。他说&ldquo;你无法根据放射性碳元素检测确定煤炭的形成时间，因为这些煤炭已经形成很久了。&rdquo;</span></div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n</div>\n<p>\n\t想要得到主持人专业的点评和意见吗？<a href=\"http://bulo.hujiang.com/menu/15399/item/898673/\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color: rgb(255,0,0);\">快来节目现场一试身手吧&gt;&gt;</span></a></p>\n<br /><center><a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p620926/#relate_articles\"><img src=\"http://en.hujiang.com/2009/images/rss_chat.jpg\" style=\"border: 0;\" /></a> <a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p620926\"><img src=\"http://en.hujiang.com/2009/images/rss_digg.jpg\" style=\"border: